<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3495] BlockJoinQuery doesn&apos;t implement boost</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3495</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;After reviewing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3494&quot; title=&quot;Remove per-document multiply in FilteredQuery&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3494&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, i checked other queries and noticed that BlockJoinQuery currently throws UOE for getBoost and setBoost:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;throw new UnsupportedOperationException(&quot;this query cannot support boosting; please use childQuery.setBoost instead&quot;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think we can safely do that in queries, because other parts of lucene rely upon this working... for example BQs rewrite when&lt;br/&gt;
it has a single clause and erases itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think we should just pass down the boost to the inner weight.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
